debrief.question: dots
debrief.answer: I felt that the computer was slightly more reliable than the human advisor but I was aware that I might have a preconception that a computer would be better at this task. I learned that both advisors were often wrong; I still think the computer was a little more reliable but am not very confident in my belief.

debrief.question: catchall
debrief.answer: The flashes were so fast I found it extremely hard to guess which box had more dots. My strategy changed over the course of the sessions as I learned that both advisors were fallible. I used them to boost my confidence when they agreed with me, but varied my approach to their advice when I was more or less confident in my initial opinion of the dot-boxes. It was an interesting challenge to work out my reliance on my own perceptions and on the advice given and to adapt; I'm not sure I made much progress though!
